detail.content: Global Politics of Green Growth | NYU Wagner                                    Jump to navigation                                                             Global Politics of Green Growth   UPADM-GP.280, 4 points.       Courses         Description |    Syllabi |    Evaluations           The quest to decrease the use of fossil fuels spurred by concerns over energy security, high prices, and climate change is now underway across the globe. The economic crisis and the desire of governments to create jobs are prompting the development and use of green technologies. This creates a new global competition for limited resources, and the race to become a leader in green tech innovation is giving rise to a series of new global political and economic realities, tensions and brewing disputes.    Prerequisites: None                     Semester     Instructor     Syllabus Link         Fall 2011 Sophia Kalantzakos Syllabus                         Semester     Instructor     Evaluation Link         Spring 2013 Sophia Kalantzakos Evaluation  Spring 2013 Zahra Ali Evaluation  Fall 2011 Kalantzakos, Sophia Evaluation

Global Politics of Green Growth | NYU Wagner                                    Jump to navigation                                                             Global Politics of Green Growth   UPADM-GP.280, 4 points.       Courses         Description |    Syllabi |    Evaluations           The quest to decrease the use of fossil fuels spurred by concerns over energy security, high prices, and climate change is now underway across the globe. The economic crisis and the desire of governments to create jobs are prompting the development and use of green technologies. This creates a new global competition for limited resources, and the race to become a leader in green tech innovation is giving rise to a series of new global political and economic realities, tensions and brewing disputes.    Prerequisites: None                     Semester     Instructor     Syllabus Link         Fall 2011 Sophia Kalantzakos Syllabus                         Semester     Instructor     Evaluation Link         Spring 2013 Sophia Kalantzakos Evaluation  Spring 2013 Zahra Ali Evaluation  Fall 2011 Kalantzakos, Sophia Evaluation
